utfx (3.0.0) xenial; urgency=medium

  * Initial debian release.
  * The requirement that data is read from and written to structures
    in sizes of the code unit is relaxed. Data can now be read from and
    written to by the byte, regarless of mode.
  * All C structures have an equivalent C++11 class.
  * The converter structure was brought about, for when processing of the
    decoded data is not required.

 -- Taylor Holberton <taylorcholberton@gmail.com>  Wed, 22 Jun 2016 22:23:10 -0400

